Temiloluwa O’Peters The Chief Executive Officer, Lagos State Lotteries Board, Abiola Are, has approved Dangote Cement Plc “Bag of Goodies 2” consumer promo. He described it as a vital private sector intervention that would reduce the adverse economic impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on Nigerians. A statement emailed to our correspondent on Sunday by a media relations official of Dangote Industries Limited, Francis Arowole-Browne, quoted Are to have said this at the unveiling of Dangote Bag of Goodies Promo Season 2 in Lagos. He commended the manufacturing giant for investing in the lives of its consumers and said their decision to make 1,000 millionaires was a testament to the company’s focus on consumers. Are said, “The promo is important especially in this time of global pandemic. Psychologically, these are things that give people hope. We are here to support the promotion.” Also speaking at the event, a representative of the Federal Competition and Consumer Protection Commission, Mrs Susie Onwuka, said that the company had followed due process in its Season 1 of the Bag of Goodies Consumer Promotion. She added that the commission would ensure the company was able to deliver what it promised the consumers. The Deputy Director/Coordinator, Nigeria Lottery Regulatory Commission, Lagos Zonal Office, Mrs Nkiru Onuzulu, said that the commission held Dangote Cement in high regard for its contribution to the general wellbeing of its consumers. In his speech, the Group Managing Director, Dangote Cement Plc, Mr Michel Puchercos, described the promo as part of the company’s strategy to provide consumers with palliatives. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 